column1: Indicator name: Greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions from agriculture  Data Source: FAO (http://www.fao.org/), FAOSTAT Agriculture database(http://faostat3.fao.org/home/E)

Description: Total greenhouse gas emissions from agriculture contain all the emissions produced in the different agricultural emissions sub-domains, providing a picture of the contribution to the total amount of GHG emissions from agriculture. GHG emissions from agriculture consist of non-CO2 gases, namely methane (CH4) and nitrous oxide (N2O), produced by crop and livestock production and management activities.

Emissions Database for Global Atmospheric Research (EDGAR), release EDGAR v5.0 (1970 - 2015) of November 2019.(http://edgar.jrc.ec.europa.eu/)

Description: The GHG total, expressed in million metric tons of CO2 equivalent, are composed of CO2 totals excluding short-cycle biomass burning (such as agricultural waste burning and Savannah burning) but including other biomass burning (such as forest fires, post-burn decay, peat fires and decay of drained peatlands), all anthropogenic CH4 sources, N2O sources and F-gases (HFCs, PFCs and SF6)of drained peatlands).
